					'You ask him. "You don''t like that Nush is in the band?"'
					*nl
					'He shakes his head. "No it''s not that, it is just those boys are trouble." Then he sighs. "Shit but who am I to talk, I was just like them at that age. I had no respect for girls either, back then. Just the way of the world I guess."'
					'"The band needs her, she writes a lot of their songs, plays guitar and sings some. I don''t think they would risk losing her." You tell him but even you are not completely convinced by your own words, you know all too well how boys are.'
					*nl
					'"Maybe you''re right, but if they ever hurt my little girl, they best run far and fast, because if I get my hands on them, they will learn what pain really means." He says in a menacing tone with a hard glint in his eyes. It reminds you that most of the adults seem to be afraid of him and talk about how dangerous of a guy he used to be. You almost feel sorry for any boy that incur his wrath, almost, but if they do, they will likely deserve it.'
